texts.text: 20w09a is the fourth snapshot for Java Edition 1.16, released on February 26, 2020,[1] which adds crying obsidian, target blocks and renames zombie pigmen among other changes.

1 Additions
1.1 Blocks
1.2 Gameplay
1.3 General
2 Changes
2.1 Blocks
2.2 Items
2.3 Mobs
2.4 Non-mob entities
2.5 Gameplay
2.6 General
3 Fixes
4 Video
5 References

Is only decorative for now, but will have uses in the future.[2]
Can be obtained by bartering with piglins.
Has a light level of 10.
Emits purple particles.
Can be moved by pistons.

Redstone component that can be activated by shooting projectiles into it.
The closer to the center the projectile hits on one of its faces, the stronger the redstone signal.
Can be crafted using a hay bale and 4 redstone dust pieces.

Added new "Bullseye" advancement.
To complete this advancement, the player has to shoot a projectile into the center of one face of a target block.
Found in the "Adventure" tab.
The recipes for crimson and warped signs have been added to the recipe book and are unlocked by having the respective planks.

Added new climbable block tag.
Includes ladders, vines, scaffolding, and weeping vines.
Used in mob pathfinding and to determine what blocks the player can climb.
Added new impact_projectiles entity tag.
Includes the arrows tag, snowballs, fireballs, small fireballs, eggs, tridents, dragon fireballs, and wither skulls.
Used to determine what entities will break chorus fruit when hit.
Added three particles for crying obsidian: dripping_obsidian_tear, falling_obsidian_tear, and landing_obsidian_tear.

Renamed to "Fungus."
Can now be added to flower pots.
Can now only be grown in huge fungi when on the same type of nylium.
Now have the replaceable plant material.

Can now be placed into flower pots.
Warped roots now have the replaceable plant material.

Are now climbable.
Now have the replaceable plant material.

Diamond axe, diamond boots, diamond helmet, diamond hoe, diamond leggings, diamond pickaxe, diamond shovel, diamond sword, golden hoe, golden pickaxe, netherite pickaxe, wooden hoe, and wooden pickaxe
Changed their textures slightly, fixing some texture inconsistencies.
Can now break nether wart blocks and warped wart blocks quickly.
Can now break soul soil quickly.
Slightly tweaked the texture. Some colors were tweaked and transparent pixels were removed.

Now have an IsImmuneToZombification data value that prevents them from zombifying in the Overworld.
Baby piglins now ride on the back of baby hoglins.

Has been renamed to "Zombified Piglin".
Updated model and texture.
The texture used is the same texture added in 20w07a.
Now checks dismount position height against entity height.

Bartering loot has been restructured to be more appealing to survival players.[1]
The new loot for bartering consists of:
Common barters (20⁄226 chance or about 8.85%): 6–10 shroomlight, 1 fire charge, 8–16 gravel, 4–10 leather, 4–10 warped fungus, 4–16 nether brick, 1 obsidian, or 1–3 crying obsidian.
Uncommon barters (10⁄226 chance or about 4.42%): 8–16 nether quartz, 5–12 glowstone dust, 2–6 magma cream, 4–8 ender pearl, or 8–24 string.
Rare barters (5⁄226 chance or about 2.21%): 1 warped nylium, 1 Fire Resistance potion or 1 Fire Resistance splash potion.
Very rare barter (1⁄226 chance or about 0.44%): 1 netherite hoe.
In this snapshot, all item amounts are 1–5 due to a bug.[3]
Piglins will now inspect gold ingots first before throwing out the item they choose to barter for the player if they're still around.
Stained glass pane recipes now only unlock when the player has the same color of stained glass in their inventory.

block.portal.travel and block.portal.trigger sounds are now part of the "ambient/environment" sound category adjustable in options.
Shearing sound category was changed from "friendly creatures" to "players" for players using shears and "blocks" for dispenser using shears.
Added potted crimson fungus, warped fungus, crimson roots, and warped roots to the flower_pots block tag.
Color now transitions smoothly between biomes.
Changed the ambient lighting in the Nether, it is now much darker.
Removed duplicate and unused textures for stripped warped logs.

55 issues fixed
From released versions before 1.16

MC-7424 – Fall damage death messages do not show the block players fall from correctly (ladders, vines, water).
MC-102319 – Nether portal trigger and travel sounds are not assigned to any sound category.
MC-111726 – Minecart dismount position always above the minecart, even if there's space next to it.
MC-137554 – Shearing sound is in the "friendly creatures" sound category.
MC-146834 – Zombie pigman's head bottom texture is flipped.
MC-147601 – Purpur pillar block top texture has not changed to a new texture.
MC-148869 – Player can clip through the ground when exiting a minecart or a boat.
MC-149042 – Minecart dismount position is not consistent.
MC-164435 – Stream sounds do not loop properly.
MC-166246 – Skeleton horses cannot be leashed.
MC-170273 – Diamond swords use the wrong pallet.
MC-170274 – Pickaxe textures are inconsistent.
MC-170556 – Hoe textures are inconsistent.

MC-170815 – Soul sand valley fossils generate duplicated/stacked.
MC-170823 – Crimson and Warped trees spawn on top of the Nether roof.
MC-170833 – Crimson fungi and warped fungi cannot be placed in flower pots.
MC-170834 – Cannot replace warped forest foliage with other blocks.
MC-170835 – Nether large fungi do not kill nylium underneath them.
MC-170842 – Potted plant models are still missing their bottom due to faulty UV.
MC-170844 – Nether sprouts do not break when their supporting block is removed.
MC-170879 – Nether fog abruptly changes color when moving across biomes.
MC-170890 – Users can get normal fire on soul soil.
MC-170904 – When viewed in 3rd person mode, the cape renders incorrectly when sneaking while wearing a chest plate.
MC-170915 – Hoglins have inconsistent texture.
MC-170932 – Cave generator will not cut through crimson_nylium and warped_nylium, leading to lots of floating nylium.
MC-170954 – Lava spreads blue fire at invalid locations.
MC-170961 – Mining speeds for breaking crimson and warped doors, trapdoors, fences, signs, stairs, and slabs are not faster with an axe.
MC-170968 – Crimson and warped fungi replace certain blocks when growing.
MC-170986 – Lava fire spread creates normal fire on soul soil.
MC-171025 – Netherite items are not pushed in flowing lava.
MC-171048 – HugeFungiConfiguration has an unused planted field.
MC-171077 – Soul fire can be /setblock on air, while normal fire cannot.
MC-171130 – Hoglin spawn egg is not sorted alphabetically in the Creative menu.
MC-171245 – Warped and crimson signs cannot be crafted.
MC-171448 – The top textures of stripped stems do not match the normal stem top textures.
MC-171457 – New fungi wrongly named.
MC-171491 – Fossils generate floating in the sky in buffet worlds.
MC-171502 – In the texture files there is 2 sets of textures for the stripped warped stem.
MC-171517 – Nylium, wart bushes, soul soil, or soul sand generate slightly below the Nether ceiling.
MC-171548 – Soul soil is not mined quicker with a shovel.
MC-171640 – Villagers, vindicators, and zombies do not properly interact with the new crimson/warped doors
MC-171731 – Huge fungi generate on the lowest nylium block.
MC-171961 – Nether wart block and warped wart block do not have a tool assigned.
MC-172084 – Soul sand and soul soil have no sounds.
MC-172090 – Piglins would rather hold a golden item than a crossbow.
MC-172096 – Baby hoglins and baby piglins do not seem to play with each other.
MC-172112 – Hoglin walking sound is subtitled as "Hoglin dies" instead of "Footsteps".
MC-172151 – Dark oak saplings are called "Jukebox/Note Blocks" in English (United Kingdom).
MC-172203 – Soul sand and soul soil have no subtitles for breaking, placing and when being walked on.
MC-172356 – Piglin admiring held gold ingot drops it when killed.
MC-172363 – Piglins are not attracted to certain golden items.
MC-172434 – Baby piglins do not sound high-pitched when zombified.
MC-172486 – Piglins drop two shields when killed while holding one in their offhand.
MC-172516 – Piglins/hoglins become persistent when within 16 blocks of a player, causing massive lag due to piling up entities.
MC-172580 – Piglin can no longer pick up items when equipped with a shield.
"It's decorative for now, but will have uses later ;)" – @kingbdogz on Twitter, February 26, 2020
